Etymology. We name this species after its type locality, Naden Village, to underscore the importance of the limestone forest in terms of biodiversity and nature conservation. From this site another new gecko species (
Cyrtodactylus rufford
) was described recently (
Luu et al . 2016
). We suggest as common names: Naden Gecko (English), Kap Ke Naden (Laotian), and Naden Gecko (German).
